        <details style="border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; border-radius: 8px; overflow: hidden;">
          <summary style="padding: 10px 12px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; color: #111827; cursor: pointer; background: #f8fafc; list-style: none;">🔌 Ingestion &amp; large files</summary>
          <ul style="margin: 0; padding: 10px 12px 12px 32px; font-size: 11px; color: #4b5563; line-height: 1.7;">
            <li><code style="background:#f1f5f9; color:#334155; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:4px; font-size:10.5px;">Connector per source</code> — OAuth2/API token, no scraping</li>
            <li><code style="background:#f1f5f9; color:#334155; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:4px; font-size:10.5px;">Streamed</code> — GB files handled in pieces, never loaded whole</li>
            <li><code style="background:#f1f5f9; color:#334155; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:4px; font-size:10.5px;">Object storage</code> — raw files in S3, not our database</li>
            <li><code style="background:#f1f5f9; color:#334155; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:4px; font-size:10.5px;">Background jobs</code> — large files never block the app</li>
          </ul>
        </details>

        <details style="border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; border-radius: 8px; overflow: hidden;">
          <summary style="padding: 10px 12px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; color: #111827; cursor: pointer; background: #f8fafc; list-style: none;">✂️ Chunking at scale</summary>
          <ul style="margin: 0; padding: 10px 12px 12px 32px; font-size: 11px; color: #4b5563; line-height: 1.7;">
            <li><code style="background:#f1f5f9; color:#334155; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:4px; font-size:10.5px;">Same principle, parallelized</code> — section-based, worker pool</li>
            <li><code style="background:#f1f5f9; color:#334155; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:4px; font-size:10.5px;">Incremental</code> — hash check skips unchanged files</li>
            <li><code style="background:#f1f5f9; color:#334155; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:4px; font-size:10.5px;">Auto-split</code> — oversized sections, consistent chunk quality</li>
          </ul>
        </details>

        <details style="border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; border-radius: 8px; overflow: hidden;">
          <summary style="padding: 10px 12px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; color: #111827; cursor: pointer; background: #f8fafc; list-style: none;">⚡ Faster retrieval, beyond CAG</summary>
          <ul style="margin: 0; padding: 10px 12px 12px 32px; font-size: 11px; color: #4b5563; line-height: 1.7;">
            <li><code style="background:#f1f5f9; color:#334155; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:4px; font-size:10.5px;">HNSW indexing</code> — fast search across millions of vectors</li>
            <li><code style="background:#f1f5f9; color:#334155; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:4px; font-size:10.5px;">Read replicas</code> — spread query load across machines</li>
            <li><code style="background:#f1f5f9; color:#334155; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:4px; font-size:10.5px;">Hybrid search</code> — vector + keyword for exact terms</li>
            <li><code style="background:#f1f5f9; color:#334155; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:4px; font-size:10.5px;">Re-ranking</code> — better relevance, no extra search pass</li>
          </ul>
        </details>

        <details style="border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; border-radius: 8px; overflow: hidden;">
          <summary style="padding: 10px 12px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; color: #111827; cursor: pointer; background: #f8fafc; list-style: none;">🗄️ Vector store at scale</summary>
          <ul style="margin: 0; padding: 10px 12px 12px 32px; font-size: 11px; color: #4b5563; line-height: 1.7;">
            <li><code style="background:#f1f5f9; color:#334155; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:4px; font-size:10.5px;">Chroma → Pinecone/Qdrant</code> — config swap, not redesign</li>
            <li><code style="background:#f1f5f9; color:#334155; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:4px; font-size:10.5px;">Independent scaling</code> — ingestion never slows queries</li>
            <li><code style="background:#f1f5f9; color:#334155; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:4px; font-size:10.5px;">Sharding</code> — index spreads across nodes</li>
          </ul>
        </details>

        <details style="border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; border-radius: 8px; overflow: hidden;">
          <summary style="padding: 10px 12px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; color: #111827; cursor: pointer; background: #f8fafc; list-style: none;">📊 Observability</summary>
          <ul style="margin: 0; padding: 10px 12px 12px 32px; font-size: 11px; color: #4b5563; line-height: 1.7;">
            <li><code style="background:#f1f5f9; color:#334155; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:4px; font-size:10.5px;">Structured logs</code> — question, distance, confidence, latency</li>
            <li><code style="background:#f1f5f9; color:#334155; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:4px; font-size:10.5px;">Dashboards</code> — accuracy, latency, cache hit rate over time</li>
            <li><code style="background:#f1f5f9; color:#334155; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:4px; font-size:10.5px;">Tracing</code> — connector → ingestion → retrieval → LLM</li>
            <li><code style="background:#f1f5f9; color:#334155; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:4px; font-size:10.5px;">Alerts</code> — confidence drift, rising "not found" rate</li>
          </ul>
        </details>

        <details style="border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; border-radius: 8px; overflow: hidden;">
          <summary style="padding: 10px 12px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; color: #111827; cursor: pointer; background: #f8fafc; list-style: none;">🛟 Recovery &amp; reliability</summary>
          <ul style="margin: 0; padding: 10px 12px 12px 32px; font-size: 11px; color: #4b5563; line-height: 1.7;">
            <li><code style="background:#f1f5f9; color:#334155; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:4px; font-size:10.5px;">Retries with backoff</code> — transient failures self-heal</li>
            <li><code style="background:#f1f5f9; color:#334155; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:4px; font-size:10.5px;">Circuit breakers</code> — graceful degradation, no cascades</li>
            <li><code style="background:#f1f5f9; color:#334155; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:4px; font-size:10.5px;">Checkpointing</code> — interrupted syncs resume, don't restart</li>
            <li><code style="background:#f1f5f9; color:#334155; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:4px; font-size:10.5px;">Backups</code> — documented restore path</li>
          </ul>
        </details>

      </div>
